Soup, stew</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">מָרַק</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(maraq)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:19\">JDG 6:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:20\">JDG 6:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:4\">ISA 65:4</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">מֶרְקָחָה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(merqachah)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek24:10\">EZK 24:10</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">נָזִיד</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(nazid)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:29\">GEN 25:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:34\">GEN 25:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:38\">2KI 4:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:39\">2KI 4:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:40\">2KI 4:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag2:12\">HAG 2:12</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">ἕψεμα</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(hepsēma)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Bel1:33\">BEL 1:33</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Description:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>Soup was a meal made by boiling vegetables and/or meat in water.</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Translation:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>The Hebrew word <em>maraq</em> refers to a stew made with meat, while the word <em>nazid</em> indicates a stew made with vegetables or legumes. Some languages will have a distinct word for each one.</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
